Even if an experimental vaccine seems so far to be capable of reducing the mortality rate of Ebola, no remedy has yet been sufficiently effective to treat the existing infection.
Even if the administration of a cocktail of antibodies, ZMapp, had first shown promising signs on the ground, formal studies have shown that its ability to limit deaths did not meet expectations.
In the PALM trial, ZMapp was used as a control, which means that scientists used it as a reference and compared the three other treatments to it.
The American Gymnastics Federation supports the letter of the United States Olympic Committee and accepts the absolute necessity of the Olympic family to promote a safe environment for all our athletes.
We agree with the statement of the USOC (United States Olympic Committee) that the interests of our athletes and our clubs, as well as their sport, could be better served. This can be done by moving forward and making significant changes within our organization, rather than revoking accreditation.
USA Gymnastics supports an independent investigation that could shed light on how the abuse described so courageously by the survivors of Larry Nassar could have gone unnoticed for so long and adopts all necessary and appropriate changes.
USA Gymnastics and the USOC have the same goal: to make gymnastics, as well as other sports, as safe as possible so that athletes can pursue their dreams in a safe, positive and responsible environment.
Throughout the 1960s, Brzezinski worked for John F. Kennedy as an advisor, and then for the administration of Lyndon B. Johnson.
During the 1976 selections, he advised Carter on foreign policy, then served as National Security Advisor (NSA) from 1977 to 1981, succeeding Henry Kissinger.
During his time at the NSA, he helped Carter to resolve diplomatically international issues such as the Camp David Accords, in 1978, the normalization of relations between the United States and China at the end of the 1970s, the Iranian revolution and its consequences such as the taking of hostages in Iran, in 1979, and the Soviet invasion of Afghanistan, in 1979.
