They found that the Sun worked according to the same basic principles as the other stars. The activity of all the stars in the system is determined by their luminosity, their rotation, and nothing else.
The luminosity and rotation are used jointly in order to determine the Rossby number of a star, which is related to the plasma flow.
As far as magnetic inversions are concerned, the smaller the Rossby number, the less active the star is.
